column2: Clear sunny day- two loons- half inch of rain on Wed. night 5:13.  Two boats.
Partly cloudy day.  Four loons were on the lake.  Three fishing boats were also on the lake.  Slight wind.  Water was a little murky.
Clear- sunny- slight wind.  Three fishing boats on the lake.  One loon on the lake.
Clear blue sky and light winds.  Ducks on the lake.  Dead walleye on the bottom of the lake  in about five feet of water.
Two fishing boats on the lake and one recreational boat.  Two loons.
Clear blue sky with light wind.  One fisherman and one recreational boater.  Four loons on the lake.
Light winds. Three fishing boats and two recreational boats.  Clear blue sky.
overcast with nne wind at 5 mph slight chop on water no activity.
Hazy sun with light southerly winds
Reading with a SW breeze and sunny skies Today was hot and humid with a westerly breeze at 5 to 10 mph. Also it was partly cloudy but mostly sunny with 2 pontoon boats and a fishing boat for traffic.
The weather was sunny with a slight SW breeze
NW breeze at 10mph- partly cloudy- with no boat traffic
Clear-calm humid day with no boat traffic on lake
Slight breeze from the SSW- mostly cloudy with no boat traffic.
Today was mostly sunny with a slight breeze from the SSW. There were no other boats on the lake.
Today was overcast after light rain. There was calm winds with no boat traffic.
With average boat traffic and winds out of the north at 5-10 mph we took our water survey with clear blue skies.
Today was sunny with a strong wind out of the south at 15 mph. There were a couple of boats but not stirring it up.
Today was mostly sunny and quite blustry. There were no other boats on the lake -but the winds were WSW gusting to 35 mph!

Today was partly to mostly cloudy with wind out of the south at 10+ mph. There was no boat traffic on the lake. I was reading the numbers while my wife- Sue- wrote down the information. Today was partly to mostly cloudy with a south wind at 10+ mph. There were no boats on the lake. My wife- Sue- wrote down the information as I gathered it.
A beautiful day on the lake! There was an even mix of sun and clouds with just a light breeze out of the south. No other boats on the lake.
Today was a south breeze at 5 to 10 mph with hazy sunshine. There were a couple of fishing boats but nobody was going fast. Yesterday was slightly busier with jet skiis.
Today was about 70 degrees with a very slight breeze from the N.E. Just a perfect morning with the exception of a lone jet ski. My wife Susan was helping as usual.
Today was humid with hazy sunshine. There were a couple of boats out and the lake is recouperating from the 4th of July week! There was a SSE wind at 10 mph or so.
Today was hot and humid with a westerly breeze at 5 to 10 mph. Also it was partly cloudy but mostly sunny with 2 pontoon boats and a fishing boat for traffic.
The weather today was breezy and overcast. The wind was out of the south at 5-10 mph. There were three other boats on the lake fishing and it was rather cool. Susie helped me today- as usual.

Another beautiful day! There were bright blue skies with puffy white clouds and a breeze coming from the north at 5 to 10 mph. The crayfishermen were on the water as well. Thanks again to my wife Susan for helping me out! The baby eagle was squawking for food but getting none.

Today was a beautiful sunny day with a few cirrus clouds not causing any haziness. We were the only boat on the water as the tests were taken. There was a cool westerly wind at 5 to 10 mph. Susan helped again.

Today with the help of my wife- Susan- we are entering our final data for the year 2013. It was not very nice on the water today. Gray and dismal with overcast skies and fog. The wind was out of the SSW at 5 to 10 mph and there were no other boats on the lake at this time.

There were two other boats on the lake- both fishing- with a significant chop on the water from the SW winds. This is our first collection of data this year. It was a late spring and weather along with family obligations kept us from getting started any sooner! The winds were from the SW at a steady 15 mph.
Today there was hazy sunshine with a SE breeze at 5 mph. We were the only boat on the lake. Sue recorded the information as I took it.
It was cloudy this afternoon and I think the secchi reading was affected. Winds were light out of the east at about 5 mph. A nice day but alittle cool.

The wind this afternoon was out of the SSE at 5 mph. There were a couple of fishing boats on the lake with one boat doing some skiing and tubing earlier. There were a few peeks on sunshine today but during this monitoring it was completely cloudy.
Sunny skies today with a slight breeze out of the SW. There were a couple of boats on the lake at the time of testing. I had help from my wife- my oldest daughter Emily- and my granddaughter Faith.
Today it was overcast with hazy sunshine. There were three other boats on the lake...all fishing. Sue was my helper again- she does a great job! The winds were light (0-5mph) and out of the NW.
There was slightly hazy sunshine today and cool for the month of July! The wind was out of the north at 5-10 mph. The crayfish boys were out and another fishing pontoon boat.

A beautiful day! Sun shine through high wispy clouds. There were four kayaks and one boat out fishing. My wife- Susan- was again helping me today. There was a light breeze out of the ENE at less than 5 mph.

There was one boat on the lake- pulling two tubers. A cool day but nice with partly cloudy- mostly sunny skies. The wind was out of the north at 5-10 mph causing a bit of a chop. We just received almost an inch of heavy rain less than 48 hours ago which might explain the decreased water clarity.

Sue and I were out on the lake alone today. We have gotten quite a bit of rain recently and today was- therefore- very foggy and overcast... a typical grey day! The wind was light out of the south at 5 mph. There were four loons near us- just being loons!?
A cool day- breezy and quiet. Sue helped me record the lake data...she is my best helper! The wind was out of the WNW at 10mph- gusting to 15mph and the skiies were partly sunny.

Sue and I went out on a friends boat today to collect our data...(ours is in winter storage). It was a gray day with no sunshine at all. There was no detectable wind as we were watched by an eagle on its' favorite branch.

My wife is helping me collect data  again this year. We had a late start due to a vacation earlier this year followed by bad weather and we were gone quite often. Let's get started! It was a totally calm morning with two fishing boats that did not interfere at all with us. It is supposed to rain this afternoon.

It was partly to mostly cloudy today. The wind was out of the NW with a speed of 10 to 15 MPH. Sue was my helper...as always! There were three boats fishing and our resident Moomba was ready to come out.
There was one other fishing boat on the lake today. Sue was my helper again as the wind came from the south at a max of 5 mph. The skies were mostly sunny.

Today was a hazy day with puffy white clouds in the mix. My wife Sue helped again...more than entering the data since I am working with bruised ribs! There were 2 fishing boats and a family swimming off of their dock. It is a warm day...80 plus out. The wind was from the SW at 5 to 10 MPH.

The lake was quite busy today. Thanks again to Sue! There was a stiff wind out of the north at 10 to 15 mph. It was partly cloudy as well. There were several vehicles on the lake- including a jet ski- 2 kayaks and 2 pontoon boats. It was windy and wavy and our lone anchor had a hard time holding!

Sue and I found it to be quite windy today. The wind was pretty much from the South at 10 to 15 mph. There were also two fishing boats (one motor trolling) and a ski boat. There was a bit of a solid cloud cover...making for a hazy sunshine.

Today was 20 degrees below normal...a blustery day at best! The winds were out of the NW at speeds of 10 to 15 mph. The crayfish boat was out this morning- but that was it. Sue and I had a difficult time starting the boat...we needed to charge the battery. It was mostly cloudy and wavy which could affect the secchi reading!
Today- with Susie's help- we found that there were no other boats on the lake. It was a beautiful morning...clear skies- and the wind was out of the South at 5 mph.
Today there was hazy sunshine with 1 other boat on the lake. The wind was out of the south at 10-20 mph. I noticed that I had a low battery signal on the temperature monitor.
There are a few puffy clouds today but mostly sunny and calm. The winds were out of the east at 0-5 mph. All I could see was one other boat that was fishing.
There were no boats on the lake today. Sue was helping again and we were working out of our canoe. The winds were from the south at 5-10 mph. It was a clear day and over 70 degrees...beautiful!

Today was a busy day- early- on the lake.  There were no boats on the lake when we took our readings.  Sue helped me- once again- and the lake has settled down! It was mostly sunny- with a NW wind at 5-10 mph. There were a few puffy clouds... a beautiful day!

Today was partly cloudy with a 50/50 ratio of sun and puffy clouds. It was a chilly wind out of the north at 5-15 mph. My wife- Sue- helped me with the data gathering and we were the only boat on the lake!

Sue helped with the data gathering and we were the only boat on the lake! It was a gray- cloudy day and the winds were calm. A couple of geese families were swimming away from "our" shore when we went down and the loons were "kinda" vocal.

Sue helped again- as always- and we did the survey after we took our granddaughter half way home. We met Emily in Portage and did lunch. The sky was about 50/50 sun and clouds and the winds were calm. There was a musky boat working the shores with two fishermen in it...a beautiful day!

Another beautiful day! Sue and I found ourselves with only one boat on the lake while we were getting our data. The wind was out of the North at 5-10 mph. It was partly cloudy and cool after yesterday's rains clouded the water!

The wind was from the North at 10-15 mph. It was warm today and Sue and I saw one other boat on the lake. I feel I must mention that we now have a jet boat on our 200 acre lake. It was partly cloudy but beautiful!

The wind was out of the WNW at 5-10 mph. It was a cloudy- gray day and there was one boat on the lake pulling a tuber. My electrician was showing up today to put in the circuit breakers in the back garage.

A beautiful evening! Sue and I collected our data after attending the St. Germain flea market. The winds were from the north at 5-10 mph. There was a pontoon boat and a fishing boat on the lake. It was a clear- sunny eve.

Rain is on the way. There were some reports of heavy rain and hail coming. It was still a lovely evening with a wind from 0-5 mph out of the south. It was mostly sunny and Sue and I observed one other boat...musky fishing.
Today Sue and I saw two other pontoon boats on the lake- one was tubing with their children. The skies were partly cloudy and the wind was out of south at 5-10 mph.

Another beautiful day! Our dehumidifier stopped running for the first time in weeks. It was a hazy sunshine kind of day with rain on the way. It was cool today with winds out of the north at 5-10 mph. The lake was busy with fishing boats...5 of them in all.

There was hazy sunshine today with the wind out of the south at anywhere from 5-15 mph. There were two boats on the lake and they were both fishing. Not a bad day considering it was Labor Day weekend!
There was one other boat on the lake fishing- and it was a beautiful but cool evening. The sky was clear and the wind was from the SW at about 5 mph.
Today was cold and blustery! It was totally gray with periods of light rain. The wind was out of the NW  at 15-20 mph- and there were no other boats on the lake!

We received about 1 1/2 inches of rain last night. The winds were out of the south at 5-10 mph today. It was mostly cloudy with hazy sunshine and about 65 degrees. Sue and I did not notice any other boats on the lake...a great day!
The sky was about 50/50 sun and puffy white clouds. The wind was from the NE at 0-5 mph. There were 3 other boats on the lake...all fishing. Beautiful day!
A truly summer-like day. Sue and I were blessed with hazy sunshine and a SW breeze at 0-5 mph. There was one other fishing boat on the lake.

Sue and I have been busy and have encountered foul weather on some satellite dates. Today- however- was beautiful. It was partly cloudy with a west wind from 0-5 mph. There was one ski boat and a fishing boat with us on the lake.
Today- Sue and I noticed one other boat on the lake. The skies were very hazy and there was a SW wind about 5-10 mph.
Sue and I found a near perfect morning! Crystal clear skies- with a wind out of the NE at 5-15 mph. There was one other boat- fishing- besides us. Beautiful!

Another stellar day with clear- blue skies. There were 3 other fishing boats beside ourselves. The wind was calm and the lake was flat. There was the appearance of 3 seagulls- which after collecting our data- I tried to chase away.

A very "still" day with hazy sunshine. It is also a solar eclipse day (noon). The lake was flat calm with 0 mph wind. If I felt anything at all- it was out of the east. I was the only boat on the lake this morning. TRANQUILL!

Another beautiful day for Sue and myself. There was a slight breeze from the east at 5 mph. The sky was mostly sunny with a few clouds starting to move in. There was one other boat (a canoe) beside us on the lake.

Hazy sky greeted Sue and myself today. Probably caused by wildfires to the west. There were no other boats on the lake and it was breezy- with winds from the south at 5-10 mph. No clouds today- but as I said- it was hazy.

The wind was from the east at 5-10 mph. There was clear blue skies overhead and gray clouds to the south. There were no other boats on the lake. By the time I was done gathering data- the wind turned from the south and the cloud cover moved in.
A beautiful day! Sue is helping again- as usual. Blue skies with just a few wispy clouds and a light breeze from the North at 0-5mph. No other motor boats on the lake- just a lone kayak.
Sue and I found the lake to be flat calm with an occasional slight breeze from the South. The sky had a hazy sunshine and there were 5 other boats out enjoying the morning.
A cool morning with sunny- clear skies. Sue and I recorded a NE wind at 5-10 mph. There were 2 other boats on the lake fishing the shores for smallmouth bass.

A beautiful day for Sue and myself. Took a dear friend to Wausau hospital- therefore- the data was taken late today. Partly cloudy skies with wispy high clouds. There were no other boats on the lake and the wind was easterly from 5-10 mph.
It was a breezy day today. Shawn helped me with gathering the data. The wind was SSE at 5-10 mph. The skies were hazy with humidity and there was one jet ski on the lake.
Sue and I were accompanied by our oldest daughter- Emily. The wind was out of the south at 5-10 mph. It was partly cloudy and there were no other boats on the lake when we were out there...BEAUTIFUL!

A beautiful day and Gannon and Nani were helping. The wind was out of the south at 0-5 mph. There were two other boats on the lake with a partly cloudy sky. The loons were out with their youngster because it was so peaceful on the lake!
Another beautiful day with Gannon and Sue as my helpers. The sky was partly cloudy and the wind was from the NW at 5-10 mph. The crayfish survey boat was the only other boat on the lake.
On my own today...finding a hazy sky (from wild fires). The wind was from the south at 0-5 mph. There were two other boats fishing but quiet in the water.

A gloomy day for Sue and myself...but we needed to get the data before the rain started! There were 2 other boats on the lake- both fishing the shores. The wind was out of the south at 5-10 mph and there was a thick overcast...not very nice!

A beautiful evening having just returned from Gov. Dodge State Park. The skies are clear with a south wind at 5-10 mph. There are two other boats on the lake that appear to be motor trolling. A beautiful evening! Sue and I just returned from camping at Gov. Dodge State Park. The skies were clear and there were two other boats on the lake motor trolling. The wind was from the south at 5-10 mph.

It was a beautiful day with one other boat on the lake. The wind was from the North at 5-10 mph. The skies were mostly sunny with a few wispy clouds. My wife- Susan- was once again my helper...bless her heart!

A late start this year with boat lift problems! Sue and I motored out today...what a beautiful day it is. There was not a cloud in the sky and the wind was from the southeast at 10-15 mph. We noticed a fishing boat and a pontoon boat on the lake...pretty quiet for a Saturday.

Another great day...no other boats on the lake at the time of our research. Sue and I noticed a slight breeze (0-5 mph) out of the southwest and it was mostly sunny and clear overhead with more clouds to the south. The lake loon family kept us company from afar.
Sue and I decided it could rain any minute this morning. The wind was from the south at 5-10 mph. The sky was completely gray and there were no boats on the lake at the time of our testing.
A beautiful day for Sue and me although- a bit breezy. The sky was mostly sunny with the winds from the SSW at 10-15 mph. There were 3 other boats on the lake- all fishing.
Today there were sprinkles early then just plain old gray- overcast skies. Sue and I noticed one other boat on the lake. The wind was brisk out of the south at 10-15 mph. Rather cool and clammy.

The lake was very quite for a Sunday afternoon. There were two other boats on the lake besides Sue and myself. The skies were solid gray clouds and it looked like it could rain any second. The wind was out of the south at 0-5 mph.
A crystal clear day with nothing but blue skies. Sue- Sophia- Gannon and I all noticed 2 other boats on the lake and a pair of kayakers. The wind was very slight at 0-5 mph from the west.

A beautiful day for Shawn- Gannon and me to gather some data. The sky was mostly sunny with a constant wind from the south west at 5-10 mph. There were no other boats on the lake and the loon was complaining about the eagle overhead.
I was by myself today. The sky was cloudy with peeks of sun. The wind was from the north at 5-10 mph. There were no other boats on the lake!

The previous two weeks were rained out. Today was cool but nice. There was one other boat on the lake- fishing. The skies were mostly sunny with a cool wind from the north at 0-5 mph. Susie helped me again as usual.

A beautiful Memorial Day morning. We are expecting rain later today but mostly clear skies for now. Sue and I noticed 2 fishing boats and a kayak while testing. The wind (breeze) was from the south at 0-5 mph.
A beautiful but "steamy" day. Sue and I noticed 2 boats and 2 kayaks on the lake. The skies were clear and the wind was from the SW at 0-5 mph.
After storms and 3 inches of rain it is cool and breezy today. Sue and I noticed one other boat on the lake and two paddle boarders. The sky was mostly cloudy with winds from the SW at 10-15 mph.

Sue and I had to gather our data early today. We were heading into Appleton as soon as we could. The sky was clear and there was not much of a wind. The faint breeze was out of the SE at 0-5 mph. There was one other boat on the lake fishing. Great day!

Another beautiful day! My son-in-law- Chris- helped today with gathering data. It was mostly sunny with a few puffy white clouds. The wind was out of the NW at 0-5 mph. There was one jet ski- two paddle boards and three other boats on the lake...relatively busy.

Kind of busy out there today (Sat. the 4th of July). The sky was mostly clear with a south wind at 0-5 mph. Hot and steamy! Sue and I a hard time counting the boats...first hard time ever. There were 7 or 8 boats- at least 6 kayaks- and 1 jet ski...still beautiful- though busy.

A cool day today for Sue and myself. There was a 10 mph breeze from the North- keeping things cool and dry. There were two boats and two kayaks out on the lake. The sky was partly cloudy/sunny about 50/50.

Today was partly cloudy with hazy sunshine coming through. The wind was from the NW at 5-10 mph. There were no other boats on the lake. We received a good amount of rain this week 5+ inches making the water deep and full of suspended erosion.

Emily- Faith- Sue and I did a joint effort to collect today's data. The sky was partly to mostly cloudy with a wind from the NW at 5-10 mph. There were 2 other boats on the lake...very quiet but nice! Emily- Faith- Sue and I did a joint data collection today. The sky was partly to mostly cloudy with a NW wind at 5-10 mph. There were 2 other boats on the lake but still quiet and nice!
A peaceful day so far. Hazy sunshine for Sue and myself with a nice SW breeze at 5-10 mph. There was just one other boat on the lake .

A little overcast today for Sue and me but pleasant. The sky gave up a hazy sunshine with the wind from the SE at 0-5 mph. There was one pontoon boat and one kayak on the lake. We think that there are two sets of loons this year.

Sue and I have been blessed with nice days- for the most part. Today was a little bit blustery with partly to mostly cloudy skies and a wind from the NW at 15-20 mph! I had to wait for the sun to "peek out" to take the best secchi reading.  There were 4 other boats on the lake...fishing.

A blustery morning with white caps greeting us on the lake. The sky was clear but hazy conditions on the horizon. Sue and I could not see any other boats on the lake (and this is Labor Day weekend). The wind was from the South at 15-20 mph.

Today was a little bit eerie for Sue and myself because of the hazy sky. Probably caused by the west coast wild fires. There was one other boat on the lake...fishing. The wind was from the SE at 0-5 mph.

A great day for collecting data! The trees are turning and the lake is finely rippled. There were 3 kayaks on the lake beside Sue and myself. The sky was clear with a slight breeze from the west at 0-5 mph. Glorious!

A blustery day for Sue and myself. We also took lake water samples today for our semi annual testing. Totally cloudy with a wind speed of 10-15 mph from the NW. There was one other boat on the lake...musky fishing.
